Usage: create_buffer_psPM_table [-help] [-file <string>] [-inverters <string>]
                                [-layer <string>] -max_target_slew <float>
                                -min_target_slew <float> [-rpt_file <string>]
                                [-slew_interval <float>] [-buffers <string> ]

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
-buffers <string>            # List of input buffers. Specified buffer should
                             # have only one input and one output.
                             # (string, optional)
-file <string>               # Suggested insertRepeater rule file name. Default
                             # is <designName>_repeater.rule. (string, optional)
-inverters <string>          # List of input inverters.  (string, optional)
-layer <string>              # Specifies the list layer names.Default is all
                             # available routing layers. (string, optional)
-max_target_slew <float>     # Maximum target slew in picoseconds.
                             # (float, required)
-min_target_slew <float>     # Minimum target slew in picoseconds.
                             # (float, required)
-rpt_file <string>           # Report file name. Default is
                             # <designName>_buffer_psPM.rpt. (string, optional)
-slew_interval <float>       # Slew range interval. Specified value should be
                             # within [0.01 1.0]. Default is 0.1. It is used
                             # for the step calculation. step =
                             # (max_target_slew - min_target_slew) *
                             # slew_interval (float, optional)